example.code:
var fight = Fight.Current;
if (fight != null)
    foreach (var f in fight.GetPlayerCats()) Mod.Log(f.Name);

GameEvents.OnHouseUpdate += e =>
{
    foreach (var cat in GameWorld.Current.GetAllCats())
        if (cat.IsOld) cat.Delete();
};

// From any thread — no GameThread.Enqueue needed:
var kitten = mom.BreedWith(dad);
if (kitten != null) Log($"Born: {kitten.Value.Name}");

// Also works inside OnHouseUpdate directly:
GameEvents.OnHouseUpdate += _ =>
{
    var cats = GameWorld.Current.GetPlayerCats();
    var mom  = cats.FirstOrDefault(c => c.Gender == 0);
    var dad  = cats.FirstOrDefault(c => c.Gender != 0);
    if (mom.IsValid && dad.IsValid)
    {
        var kitten = mom.BreedWith(dad);
        if (kitten.HasValue) Log($"Born: {kitten.Value.Name}");
    }
};

// Iterate all furniture and place any pile items into a room
foreach (var f in house.GetFurniture())
    if (f.IsInPile) { f.SubName = "Floor1_Large"; f.PosX = 50; f.PosY = 50; }

// Find and modify a specific item
var item = house.FindFurniture(typeId);
if (item.IsValid) { item.Rotation = 2; item.PosX = 100; }

var item = house.FindFurniture(typeId);
if (item.IsValid)
{
    item.SubName  = "Floor1_Large";
    item.PosX     = 100.0;
    item.PosY     = 200.0;
    item.Rotation = 2;
}

// Add and immediately place in a room
if (house.AddFurniture("set_80s_bed"))
{
    var items = house.GetFurniture();
    var item  = house.FindFurniture(items[^1].TypeId);
    if (item.IsValid)
    {
        item.SubName  = "Floor1_Large";
        item.PosX     = 50.0;
        item.PosY     = 50.0;
        item.Rotation = 0;
    }
}

member.summary:
SDL3 input access: frame-rate polling and event subscriptions via .


Polling — call anytime, returns the current state of keyboard/mouse:


if (GameInput.IsKeyDown(SDL_Scancode.Space)) { /* ... */ }
var (mx, my) = GameInput.GetMousePos();




Events — subscribe via  for per-event callbacks:


GameEvents.OnKeyDown += e => { if (e.Scancode == SDL_Scancode.F1) DoThing(); };
GameEvents.OnMouseButtonDown += e => { if (e.Button == SDL_MouseButton.Right) DoThing(); };




⚠️ All event callbacks run on the game render thread. To mutate game state
(cats, house, etc.) from an input handler, dispatch via GameThread.Post(...).

example.code:
// Iterate all cats, alive or dead, and call Delete() on the ones you want removed
foreach (var cat in GameWorld.Current.GetAllCats())
    if (cat.IsOld) cat.Delete();

member.summary:
Overwrites the UTF-16 glaiel::wstring at  with .
Handles SSO (≤ 7 wide chars inline) and existing heap allocations.
//TEST

Unified entry point for reading and writing GON/CSV data from the game's live GPAK archive.

Reads always reflect the current state of native game memory — there is no stale snapshot.
Writes go directly to the game's native C++ objects — changes are visible in
stats, tooltips, and gameplay immediately without any extra step.

Read:

var root    = Gon.From("data/items/weapons.gon");
string name = root["sword"]["name"].AsString();
int damage  = root["sword"]["damage"].AsInt(10);

// Navigate in one call:
int damage = Gon.Get("data/items/weapons.gon/sword/damage").AsInt(10);


Write (direct — game sees it immediately):

var root = Gon.From("data/items/weapons.gon");
root["sword"]["damage"].Set(999);   // writes to GPAK + SpawnDB in one call


Map to a class:

record Weapon(string Name, int Damage);
var w = Gon.From("data/items/weapons.gon")["sword"].As<Weapon>();


Iterate:

Gon.From("data/item_setbonuses.gon").ForEach(block =>
    Log($"set {block.Id}: {block["name"].AsString()}"));


CSV localization:

var loc = Gon.CsvDict("data/text/combined.csv");
string label = loc.TryGetValue("SETBONUS_SCRAP_NAME", out var v) ? v : "Scrap";

Registers  to be called once the game's GPAK is fully loaded
(GON files are available). If the GPAK is already ready, the callback is called immediately.

Use this instead of putting retry logic in your mod:

protected override void OnLoad()
{
    Gon.OnReady(() => {
        _myData = BuildMyData();
        Log($"Data loaded: {_myData.Count} entries");
    });
}

Mutable, tree-structured representation of a GON (Glaiel Object Notation) value.

A node is either:
  - a leaf  — has a string value  (name "sword_name_key")
  - a block — has child nodes      (weapon_sword { name "..." damage 10 })

Reading GON data:

var weapons = Gon.From("data/items/weapons.gon");
string name   = weapons["weapon_sword"]["name"].AsString();
int    damage = weapons["weapon_sword"]["damage"].AsInt(10);


Writing GON data — writes directly to game memory:

var weapons = Gon.From("data/items/weapons.gon");
weapons["weapon_sword"]["damage"].Set(999);   // game sees it immediately
weapons["weapon_sword"]["name"].Set("Legendary Sword");


The indexer (node["key"]) uses get-or-create — accessing a missing key
auto-adds an empty child.  Use  to probe without side effects.

Deserialises this block's fields into a new instance of .
Alias for  with a cleaner name.

record Weapon(string Name, int Damage);
var w = Gon.From("data/items/weapons.gon")["sword"].As<Weapon>();

Parses  and appends every top-level block as a new child.

If this node was obtained via  and its file path maps to a
SpawnDB catalog (e.g. data/items/weapons.gon → items), each block
is also injected into the live SpawnDB so the game sees it immediately. The entry
is persisted so it survives SpawnDB rebuilds (save/load cycles).

For paths that do not map to any catalog (e.g. mod config files), the blocks are
added to the managed tree only — readable via  and indexing.

Registers this node as the live representation of its file path so that subsequent
 calls return the same instance, preserving any
 modifications you make on the added children.

Returns this for chaining.


// Add a new item to an existing game catalog — effective immediately:
Gon.From("data/items/weapons.gon").Add(@"
    MySword { name MY_SWORD_NAME  rarity rare  kind weapon  str 5 }
");

// Add mod config data (no SpawnDB involvement):
Gon.From("mods/mymod/config.gon").Add(@"
    Settings { difficulty 3  multiplier 1.5 }
");
int diff = Gon.From("mods/mymod/config.gon")["Settings"]["difficulty"].AsInt(1);

Parses  as a GON document and injects every top-level
block into the catalog at .

Typical usage:

  string gonText = "MySword { name MY_SWORD_NAME rarity 2 kind weapon }";
  NativeGonWriter.InjectGon(gameBase, sdPtr + SPAWN_DB_ITEMS_OFFSET, gonText);


Returns the number of top-level nodes successfully injected (0 on failure).

example.code:
private static HookSlot _hook;

protected override unsafe void OnLoad()
    => _hook = Hook(GameAddressMap.FN_APPLY_DAMAGE, (nint)(delegate* unmanaged<nint,nint,void>)&HookFn);
